- From your Prism Central (PC) dasbboard - Unified Storage - Files
- Click your File Server (ex: labFS) - Share & Exports - Click New Share or Export
  * Name                    : laravel
  * Size                    : 10 GB
  * Primary Protocol Access : NFS
  * General Settings        : Default (no change)
  * Next
  * NFS Protocol Access     : Default (no change)
  * Next
  * Create
- Click your new laravel share
  * Copy the Mount Path (ex: labFS.ntnxlab.local:/laravel)

- From Code Proxy (bastion)
  sudo mkdir /mnt/laravel
  sudo mount -t nfs labFS.ntnxlab.local:/laravel /mnt/laravel
  cd /mnt/laravel

          volumeMounts:
          - name: laravel-persistent-storage
            mountPath: /app/public/images/nfs
      volumes:
      - name: laravel-persistent-storage
        persistentVolumeClaim:
          claimName: laravel-pv-claim-nfs
